# QMS Backend Linux Deployment Guide

This guide details how to deploy the QMS Python backend on your Linux server. Because your displays and staff panels will run from Windows PCs, you **do not** need to copy or migrate any over any Windows-specific `.bat` or AutoHotkey (`.ahk`) scripts.

## Will PM2 and Apache cause issues?
**No, they will not cause issues, and PM2 is actually a huge advantage.**

1.  **Port Conflicts:** Apache typically binds to port `80`/`443`, and your Node/Express apps likely use ports like `3000` or `8080`. Your QMS Flask app defaults to port `5000`. As long as port `5000` is open and not in use by your Express apps, they will run perfectly side-by-side. 
2.  **Using PM2 Instead of Systemd:** While your `linux_deploy` folder contains a Systemd `qms.service` file, since you already have **PM2** installed, you can use it to manage your Python app! PM2 is fantastic at handling the exact `os._exit(1)` crash induced by your auto-updater and will reboot the server instantly, just like the `.bat` file did on Windows.

