## Client Adjustments (Windows PCs)
Your Windows client machines running the displays will no longer need `1.Start-Server.bat` since the server is hosted elsewhere. 

You must open the `2.LaunchDisplay.bat` and `3.LaunchPanel.bat` files on the Windows machines and **update the hardcoded IP address in those files** to point to your new Linux server's IP address or domain name.

```bat
:: Change this:
"http://10.78.115.21:5000/display?kiosk=true"

:: To your Linux Server IP or Domain Name:
"http://<LINUX_SERVER_IP>:5000/display?kiosk=true"
```
